
ASSIGNMENT 1 - INSTALLATION AND SETUP

My Environment
--------------
  OSX 10.11.4
  Node.js 6.3.0
  MongoDB 3.2.8
  

3-Step Installation
-------------------

   1. Install Node.js
   
      OSX :
      $ brew install node

      Linux :
      Depending on the package manager, follow the instructions on https://nodejs.org/en/download/package-manager/


   2. Install and Run MongoDB

      OSX :
      $ brew install mongodb
      $ sudo brew services start mongodb

      Linux :
      Depending on the distribution, follow the instructions on https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/administration/install-on-linux/


   3. In the root directory of the project, run

      $ npm install

      This should install all dependencies. (try with sudo in case of errors)



Running the web app
-------------------

   -> Start the node server. In the root directory of the project, run

      $ node app.js

      You can access it at http://localhost:8000



MongoDB shell
-------------

   -> Quick-start guide to working with MongoDB - https://docs.mongodb.com/getting-started/shell/introduction/

